sec.p:
The external morphology was observed with a dissecting stereoscope (SteREO Discovery V20, Zeiss and Leica Mz Apo). The following measurements were made with an ocular micrometer:
total length, length from apical margin of clypeus to apex of elytra (TL);
total width, width across both elytra at widest part (TW = EW);
height, from the highest part of the beetle to elytral outer margins (TH);
head width in a frontal view, widest part including eyes (HW);
pronotal length, from the middle of anterior margin to the base of pronotum (PL);
pronotal width at widest part (PW);
elytral length, along the suture, from the apex to the base including the scutellum (EL). Male and female genitalia were dissected, cleared in a 10% solution of NaOH by boiling for several minutes, and examined with an Olympus BX51 and Leica compound microscopes.
